abstract_ssm: Copy negatives and modern prints of photographs taken by Richard Hoe Lawrence (1858–1936) of the slum conditions on Manhattan's Lower East Side at the end of the 19th century. Social reformer Jacob A. Riis used a number of Lawrence's images in his lectures on "The Other Half." In addition to general street scenes and Coney Island outings, the collection includes views of early baseball games at the Polo Grounds, the aftermath of the Blizzard of 1888, and the celebrations marking the 1889 centennial of George Washington's first inauguration.
